ltl2rabin

Class SubAutomaton

  • Object
    • ltl2rabin.Automaton<T,U>
      • ltl2rabin.RabinAutomaton<List<MojmirAutomaton.State<PropEquivalenceClass,Set<String>>>,Set<String>>
        • ltl2rabin.SubAutomaton

  • public class SubAutomaton
extends RabinAutomaton<List<MojmirAutomaton.State<PropEquivalenceClass,Set<String>>>,Set<String>>
    SubAutomata are Rabin automata that are constructed for a G-subformula. A GDRA.State has a collection of SubAutomaton.States. SubAutomata provide the GDRA with valuable information that is used to construct the acceptance condition of the GDRA. A SubAutomaton.State represents a ranking of MojmirAutomaton.States.

    The failMerge(int, Set) and succeed(int, Set) methods generate the acceptance sets for a given rank and set of G-subformulas. Unlike for MojmirAutomatons, acceptance is defined for transitions, not states.

    See Also:

      • failMerge

        public ImmutableSet<SubAutomaton.Transition> failMerge(int rank,
                                                       Set<G> curlyG)
        This method returns the combination of fail and merge(i) for a given rank i and a set of G subformulas. It makes use of computing caches, so the first call will be the (by far) most expensive.
        Parameters:
        rank - The requested merging rank
        curlyG - The set of G subformulas that hold
        Returns:
        The union of fail and merge(i)
